Final Blender Scene – 3D Environment Design

📌 Project Overview

This project showcases a basic 3D environment created using Blender as part of the IEEE VR Workshop. The goal was to understand the fundamentals of 3D modeling, object placement, and scene composition.

The scene consists of simple geometric objects such as cubes, spheres, and planes, combined to form a visually structured environment. Basic lighting and camera positioning were also applied to enhance the overall presentation.

🎯 Objectives

Learn the Blender interface and navigation in 3D space
Understand object creation and transformations (Move, Rotate, Scale)
Apply basic materials and lighting
Create and render a complete 3D scene
🛠️ Tools & Technologies Used

Blender (3D Modeling & Rendering)
GitHub (Project hosting and version control)
🧱 Project Components

Cube – Used as the base structure or object
Sphere – Added to enhance visual complexity
Plane – Used as ground surface
Lighting Setup – Basic light source for rendering
Camera Setup – Positioned to capture the final scene
